  <!-- Help / How it works Guide Overlay Modal -->
  <div
    id="how-it-works-modal"
    class="fixed inset-0 bg-primary/20 backdrop-blur-sm z-50 flex items-center justify-center p-4 transition-all duration-300 hidden"
  >
    <div class="bg-canvas rounded-2xl max-w-lg w-full p-6 border border-hairline shadow-modal flex flex-col gap-4 animate-scale-in max-h-[85vh] overflow-y-auto">
      <div class="flex justify-between items-center pb-2 border-b border-hairline-soft">
        <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-primary">How the Auto Loan Suite Works</h3>
        <button
          type="button"
          id="close-modal-btn"
          class="text-stone hover:text-primary transition-all text-lg cursor-pointer"
        >
          ✕
        </button>
      </div>

      <div class="text-xs text-slate leading-relaxed flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-primary">1. Basic Finance Terminology</h4>
        <p>
          Your monthly payment is calculated based on the net loan amount. Net loan amount is the Vehicle Price, minus your Down Payment, minus any Trade-in Value, plus any Sales Taxes and dealer documentation / registration fees.
        </p>

        <h4 class="font-semibold text-primary">2. Dynamic Down Payment Calculations</h4>
        <p>
          Toggle between entering a fixed dollar amount ($) or a percentage of the vehicle price (%). Changing the vehicle price will keep your percentage option proportional or your fixed dollar option static, adjusting other metrics automatically.
        </p>

        <h4 class="font-semibold text-primary">3. Balloon Payments</h4>
        <p>
          A balloon payment is a larger-than-usual one-time payment due at the end of your loan term. By reserving a portion of the principal to be paid as a lump sum at the end, your regular monthly payments are significantly reduced. Interest is still paid on the balloon amount throughout the term.
        </p>

        <h4 class="font-semibold text-primary">4. Effective APR Calculation</h4>
        <p>
          Unlike standard calculators that display the nominal rate, our engine computes a true Effective APR (Annual Percentage Rate) by solving for the internal rate of return (IRR). This accounts for front-end documentation and registration fees, showing you the real economic rate of borrowing.
        </p>
      </div>
      <button
        type="button"
        id="modal-ok-btn"
        class="button-primary text-xs py-2 px-5 mt-2 self-end cursor-pointer"
      >
        Got it
      </button>
    </div>
